      I find the idea of a &quot;fallen nature&quot; very interesting from the standpoint of how all of humanity (from a theological point of view) suffers a single condition base upon the alleged actions of two individuals. So god condemed every person from Adam and Eve onward because those two failed to behave? Do you really see that as justice? And, for that matter what does that say of the character of the individual who established the &quot;rule&quot; to begin with? After all, god knew before Adam and Eve were created that they would partake of the forbidden fruit, right? No, the tale told of our so-called fallen nature is just too convenient for the story teller and does not do an adequate job at explaining &quot;evil&quot; in the world and &quot;justice&quot;. <br>
<br>
       Why do we associate truth with pain and/or suffering?  The Bible isn't my expertise but, we have free-will and can choose to drive a hot wire coat hanger in our schlongs if we so choose.  Call it pain if you want.  That recognition of a resulting feeling will be your reality.  However, the pain(feeling) is a result of a choice made which wasn't very thoughtful.  Hence, the answers are in the truth.  The reality of those answers don't always paint a pretty picture(although the picture of someone's face as a result of the 'coat hanger' incident is pretty funny, while the picture of it's insertion is not).  This moron made a choice which had very litle balance of thought and feeling(in its non-perverse form, truth and love)  I'm not a very good writer so I'm not sure if the correlations are clear.  Anyway, the moral of the story is;  Hot wire coat hanger inda pp=truth(not just pain). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  HOWEVER, in order to love someone you must 'truth' them as well.  Call it punishment, discipline if you want. I guess it is, but ultimately it is truth is for one's own good.  Do I feel like God punishes me or disciplines me or 'truths' me?  Yea I do, because I ask for it.  THIS is why so many peps have bad feelings about God and want to punch him in his jock.  Why did your parents make you clean your room, wash behind your ears, not open presents until christmas day, teach you good manners, and/or not drop you in a dumpster when you pissed them off for the first time?  'cause they love you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    When you were a teenager why did you get pissed off all the time when they said, &quot;clean your room before you go out&quot;  or, &quot;stop ass-fucking the neighbors dog&quot;  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smoki