As scary as it sounds to hear myself say it, I really don't believe in any afterlife (atleast not any that I have heard or thought of before), they don't make any sense.  I don't think it's that we cannot comprehend what it is, it just is not logical, or even emotionally logical.<br>
<br>
So after we die and go to this wonderful place called &quot;heaven&quot; while people alive on Earth are left to suffer over the loss of a friend or loved one?  In this &quot;heaven&quot; we are seperate from the ones we care most about? Why would anyone call that heaven?<br>
<br>
The normal response seems to be &quot;we will have God to love&quot; or something, well, sorry but that just isn't what I would consider heaven, being taken away from everyone I care about.<br>
<br>
If we are so happy in heaven that would mean that our feelings on this Earth are false, it rips apart everything we currently know about emotions.<br>
<br>
So, who knows what happens to us, but I highly doubt there is any magical place full of happiness.  I don't like saying it, or thinking about it, because it always leads me to the same conclusion. <p>Tuan {Cupcakes} the Vicar</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulurikeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurikeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/29/01 8:37:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://server2048.virtualave.net/neplusultra/images/Links/c_necromancer.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Life after death</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;And actually, I didn't view your questions as retorical at all. [...] You might think they are retorical, but many people don't.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
